    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-12-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="240"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d240">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 8.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Hammond</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Waddington</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Foreign Office,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-12-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 12, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I am directed by Earl Russell to transmit to you
                    herewith, to be laid before Secretary Sir George Grey, copies of papers, as
                    marked in the margin,<note n="*" xml:id="d240fn1">Nos. 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, and
                        9:</note> respecting the enlistment at Queenstown of various British
                    subjects to serve on board the United States steam vessel-of-war the
                    Kearsarge.</p>
                <p>The law officers are of opinion that the men who so enlisted on board the
                    Kearsarge should be prosecuted;under the foreign enlistment act; and Lord
                    Russell directs me to say that he is of opinion that such prosecution should be
                    instituted as soon as sufficient evidence is collected to sustain it.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>E. HAMMOND.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
